{
  "stem": "3206.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was never-- because nobody never had nothing, nobody-- everybody was eating when we came, when we brought the bread.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So everybody was equally divided the bread.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And whatever was there to eat, there was no jealousy between one another, you know.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was lovingly, you know that we were-- everybody was for everybody.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And whenever they made-- $1 or $2, or whatever it is-- they would share.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this was the life, what went down in Poland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, every-- every Saturday.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Saturday, Friday night, all the holidays, and everything-- there was not a day that I didn't go.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't have no choice, whether I liked it or not.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have to go.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not the older brothers-- they didn't-- they didn't participate in those things, because they were already like the bread winners, so he couldn't say to them, you have to go, you have to do.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they went on their own, and they did whatever they wanted.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jewish.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Jewish papers.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The street?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The street was like-- the whole street was called [NON-ENGLISH], you know, like the synagogue was there.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "From my house to go to the synagogue was about five minutes.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was the only beautiful synagogue in the city, not just in the city of Staszow but in the whole Poland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One of the nicest synagogues there is, and near the synagogue was a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, like another [NON-ENGLISH], like a gathering.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were davening in that-- not in that shul, because this shul was a Conservative shul.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, when something came out, you know, to celebrate, like, the first of May or the third of May-- Poland, we were celebrating 3rd of May.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so they had the celebration at shul with the hazzan and the Polish dignitaries from city.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
